  <h2>How do you integrate the syslog logs with Wazuh?</h2>

  <p>
    Add the new log files to the Wazuh agent so it monitors them and forwards them to the SIEM server.
  </p>

  <!-- Bloque de codigo bloqueado -->
  <div class="locked-code-block relative my-6">
    <div style="background:#0f1419;padding:16px;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;filter:blur(3px);user-select:none;pointer-events:none;">
      <pre style="margin:0;"><code style="color: #e5e7eb;"># Edit /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf
# Add inside &lt;ossec_config&gt;:

&lt;localfile&gt;
  &lt;log_format&gt;syslog&lt;/log_format&gt;
  &lt;location&gt;/var/log/remote/nas.log&lt;/location&gt;
&lt;/localfile&gt;

&lt;localfile&gt;
  &lt;log_format&gt;syslog&lt;/log_format&gt;
  &lt;location&gt;/var/log/remote/router.log&lt;/location&gt;
&lt;/localfile&gt;

# Restart the agent
systemctl restart wazuh-agent</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center" style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.6); border-radius: 8px;">
